cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on comparing different networking topologies for data centers in the context of fog computing. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the performance and energy efficiency of data center designs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper utilizes Mixed Integer Linear Programming models to optimize the data center design. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the design of a server-centric PON-based data center architecture. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper discusses completion time results for MapReduce workloads.
